The paper deals with the design of network codes for packet line networks, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the codes, which could fall under distributed systems (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a new coding scheme, which could fall under computer communication (cs.CC).
